The course introduces the vocabulary related to the following topics: greeting, presentation; descent, nationalities, languages; address, phone numbers; professions; family; in a cafe / restaurant / bar; leisure time, hobbies, everyday activities; time, weekdays, date; in hotel, prices, room description; in a foreign city, asking directions.
Grammar: verbs 'essere', 'avere'; articles; adjectives; nouns; regular verbs: present tense; demonstrative pronouns questo/questa; prepositions; questions; pronouns (pronomi indiretti); adverbs; use of c`è/ci sono; irregular verbs: stare, fare, volere, andare, uscire, potere, venire, dovere, sapere.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at the systematic development of all four language skills - reading, writing, listening, speaking - through a wide variety of tasks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the students will be able to:
- understand simple texts (both oral and written) in Italian 
- use the vocabulary and grammar covered during the course in simple everyday situations
- can compose simple texts
